post_cb({"31191072": {"ParentId": "31190982", "CommentCount": "6", "Body": "<p>From [class.base.init]:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_31190982_31191072_0\">non-static data members are initialized in the order they were declared in the class definition\n  (again regardless of the order of the mem-initializers).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In this case, the ordering would be equivalent to:</p>\n<pre><code>int a = 1;\nint b = 2;\nint c;\nint d = 4;\nc = 3;\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2069064", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "31191072", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2015-07-02T17:33:14.203", "LastActivityDate": "2015-07-02T17:33:14.203"}, "31190982": {"CommentCount": "1", "ViewCount": "60", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "560648", "CreationDate": "2015-07-02T17:28:20.823", "LastActivityDate": "2015-07-02T17:44:45.523", "Title": "C++11: Body of class initialization assignment order", "AcceptedAnswerId": "31191072", "LastEditDate": "2015-07-02T17:41:32.380", "Id": "31190982", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>Say I have a class of the form</p>\n<pre><code>class MyClass\n{\n    int a = 1;\n    int b;\n    int c;\n    int d = 4;\n    MyClass() : b(2)\n    {\n        c = 3;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>What is the order of the assignment of <code>a,b,c,d</code>? Now I know for sure (from older C++) that <code>b</code> will be assigned before <code>c</code>. But what about the others with respect to the latter?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><initialization>", "OwnerUserId": "1317944", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_31190982_31191072_0": {"section_id": 438, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n3337": {"so_31190982_31191072_0": {"section_id": 429, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}, "n4659": {"so_31190982_31191072_0": {"section_id": 458, "quality": 1.0, "length": 14}}}});